The Daily Monitor newspaper has identified the judge as Paul Gadenya. He was previously the chief registrar of the judiciary. The newspaper quotes a police spokesperson as saying the cause of the accident is still under investigation. A hospital official is quoted as saying the judge was in a life-threatening condition and will be air-lifted to the capital, Kampala, for further treatment. The Uganda Red Cross tweeted photos of the wreckage of the judge's car. --BBC--